            <h4>Permitted Content
                </h4>
            
                <ul style="margin-left: 2.5rem;">
                    <li>In the submission rounds, participants are required to turn in solutions to any one of the problems. 
                    Round 1 is the first submission round (SR1), and Round 2 is the second submission round (SR2).</li>
                    <li>The content in the submission rounds will permit representative media such as <u>text, images, and videos.</u></li>
                <li>Additional media such as CAD renders, python simulations, and other such representation is permitted; however, it is advised to include screen captures of these instead of the complex files in your presentations. </li>
            <li>  It is advised to utilise ample visual media to demonstrate experiments which are backed with data. We also expect to view this data in charts, graphs, and other representations.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    Utilising the work of other researchers as a reference is permitted,<em> only so long as the citation is mentioned. </em> It is advised to contribute original scientific work, though. 
                    Any plagiarism will result in an <strong> immediate elimination</strong>. 
                </p>

                
