                <h4>Evaluation Board
                </h4>
                <p>The Evaluation Board is nominated and organized by the Tournament Committee. The Evaluation Board is composed of team leaders, independent jurors and past IYPT participants. The Jury consists of at least two members, if possible from different IYPT seasons.</p>

                <h4> Agenda of the Physics Fight Rounds
                </h4>
                <strong>Round 3 - Physics Fight Round
                </strong>

                <p><em>Round 3 will consist of participants that clear the second submission round</em> and enter the first physics fight round. It is a closer representation of the IYPT’s Physics Fight Format. 
                </p>

                <ul style="margin-left: 2.5rem;">
                    <li>The basic flow of a round toggles between a Reporter and an Opponent. The Reporter presents their solution on a given problem. This is called the <em>Presentation</em> of the report.
                    </li>

                    <li>This is followed by the Opponent following up with a few questions - <em>Questions of the Opponent to the Reporter and answers of the Reporter.</em> After these questions, the Opponent gets 5 minutes to prepare for their presentation. 
                    </li>
                    <li>The Opponent then reviews the Reporter’s work in what is called <em>Opponent Speech.</em> </li>
                    <li>This is finally concluded by a session in which the Reporter and Opponent both have the floor together, discussing the physics of the problem to each other as if they were in a coffee shop - <em>Discussion between the Reporter and the Opponent.</em>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h4>Grading</h4>

                <p>After each stage the Evaluation Board grades the participants,
                     taking into account all presentations, questions and answers to the questions, and participation in the discussion. 
                    <br>
                    The scoresheet and metrics for the basis of review will be updated according to the rounds. 

                    

                </p>
